Introduction
We would like to be transparent about our business and explain our technology in plain language so that users can understand how our services process personal data. This Privacy Policy describes Adform´s practices and policies with regard to the use and processing of data when providing online advertising services for the world’s largest websites and advertisers (hereinafter collectively referred to as "Services").
If you wish to find out more about Adform's processing in the context of its website and/or corporate business, please see the following
link
.
In specific Service and data processing scenarios, Adform and its clients and/or partners may act as joint controllers which – however – ultimately has no effect on exercising your data subject rights as described in the section ‘Your Data Protection Rights’ below.
If you want to find out more about the concept of joint controllership, what processing is affected and how this is managed at Adform, please visit
this link
.
What Information Do We Collect and Use
1. Reporting, measurement, forecasting, attribution
Brief explanation
Specific processing activities may be, for example:
We use combined data from cookies and the number of impressions to predict user/audience trends.
We gather IDs when a user visits an advertiser's website through tracking the user’s online activity.
For more information, please read here.
Data Categories
1st Party IDs, Cookie IDs, and technical data related to these IDs (e.g. impressions, clicks, conversions, approximate geolocation, timestamp, URL, device information, browser information), IP address.
Related Adform Product and/or Service
Buy Side, Sell Side, DMP.
Legal bases
We process this data by default on the basis of our legitimate interest. However, the publisher on whose site we are integrated with our product or service can decide to obtain your consent. In this case, we process the data based on your consent.
2. Improve online advertising experience and efficiency (IAB Purpose 2, Purpose 10)
Brief explanation
The ads you see on the website or app are chosen based on the basic information mentioned. This means that we may use the site you're on, the kind of device you're using, and your general location. We might also look at what you're interested in or what you've looked at before based on your interactions with the website or app to make sure you don't see the same ad too many times. We may also use it to show ads in a certain order, show ads you might like, or figure out the best time to show an ad or to make our ads work better and to make your online experience better by improving our products and services.
Data Categories
Same as in No.1.
Related Adform Product and/or Service
Buy side, Ad server.
Legal bases
We process this data by default on the basis of our legitimate interest. However, the publisher on whose site we are integrated with our product or service can decide to obtain your consent. In this case, we process the data based on your consent.
3. Fraud prevention and security (IAB Special Purpose 1)
Brief explanation
Your personal data can be used to monitor for and prevent unusual and possibly fraudulent or unlawful activity (e. g. to ensure that the ads are clicked upon by real people, and not bots), and ensure systems and processes work properly and securely.
Data categories
Online identifier (e. g. cookie ID, mobile advertising ID), browser information (e. g. URL/domain; time stamp, user agent, IP address).
Related Adform Product and/or Service
Buy side, sell side, Ad server.
Legal bases
Legitimate Interests.
4. Develop and Improve products (IAB Purpose 10)
Brief explanation
Personal data about how you use Adform clients' websites or apps, like how you engage with ads or content, can be really valuable for improving Adform products and services and creating new ones based on users’ activity online.
Data Categories
1st Party IDs, Cookies IDs and other identifiers as applicable, as well as real-time data (e. g. information about the page content, app type).
Related Adform Product and/or Service
Buy Side, Sell Side, Ad server, DMP.
Legal bases
We process this data by default on the basis of our legitimate interest. However, the publisher on whose site we are integrated with our product or service can decide to obtain your consent. In this case, we process the data based on your consent.
5. Synchronize our Service with other online advertising services (Link different End User devices) (IAB Feature 2)
Brief explanation
We might use Cookie IDs and other IDs to connect our Service with other online advertising services. This is an essential part of the digital advertising world because it helps our clients combine data from different advertising service providers. No other personal data is used for this purpose.
Data Categories
1st Party IDs, Cookies IDs and other identifiers as applicable.
Related Adform Product and/or Service
Buy Side, Sell Side, Ad server, DMP.
Legal bases
We process this data by default on the basis of our legitimate interest. However, the publisher on whose site we are integrated with our product or service can decide to obtain your consent. In this case, we process the data based on your consent.
6. Comply with legal obligations, especially processing data subjects‘ requests
Brief explanation
We may process your personal data to comply with our legal obligations, in particular to ensure that the data subject requests received from you are dealt in a lawful and suitable manner according to the deadlines established in the applicable data protection laws.
Data Categories
1st Party IDs, Cookies IDs and other identifiers as applicable.
Related Adform Product and/or Service
Buy Side, Sell Side, Ad server, DMP.
Legal bases
Legal obligation, legitimate interest.
7. Creation of an End User personalized advertising profile (IAB Purpose 3)
Brief explanation
We collect information about your actions on our clients' websites or apps, like the content you view or data we receive from our clients. This data may be combined with your previous actions or those of similar users. It helps us create or enhance a profile about you, including your potential interests and personal characteristics. This profile can be used to show you more relevant ads based on your interests.
Data categories
1st Party IDs, Cookie IDs, and technical data related to these IDs (e.g. impressions, clicks, conversions, approximate geolocation, timestamp, URL, device information, browser information), IP address.
Related Adform Product and/or Service
Buy side, sell side, Ad serving
Legal bases
Consent
8. Selection of personalized and/or contextual advertisements (IAB Purpose 4)
Brief explanation
Ads you see on our clients' websites or apps are determined by your advertising profiles, which are shaped by your activity on these platforms, as well as other websites or apps, your interests, and personal information.
Data categories
1st Party IDs, Cookie IDs, and technical data related to these IDs (e.g. impressions, clicks, conversions, approximate geolocation, timestamp, URL, device information, browser information), IP address.
Related Adform Product and/or Service
Buy side, ad serving.
Legal bases
Consent.
9. Use limited data to select advertising (IAB Purpose 2, Special Purpose 2)
Brief explanation
Ads on our clients' websites and apps may be tailored based on limited data, such as the site or app you're using, your general location, device type, and your interaction with content. This customization helps limit the frequency of ad displays.
Data categories
1st Party IDs, Cookie IDs, and technical data related to these IDs (e.g. impressions, clicks, conversions, approximate geolocation, timestamp, URL, device information, browser information), IP address.
Related Adform Product and/or Service
Buy side, sell side, ad serving.
Legal bases
Legitimate interests.
10. Save and communicate privacy choices User choices
Brief explanation
In order for Adform to respect user’s choices, it has to first know what those choices are. The storing and communicating of user choice signals (for instance in the form of TCF Strings), ensure that the choices of users can be respected and that Users do not have to make those choices again on each subsequent use of the relevant digital property.
This results in Adform’s recording of (and gaining of access to) consent signals, objections and user preference, for instance by means of TC Strings within the framework of the Transparency and Consent Framework (TCF). The user choice signals therefore represent the giving, refusing or withdrawing of consent by users and the exercise of their right to object.
Data Categories
General metadata about the website operator that indicate its implementation with the TCF, this include points such as ID of the CMP, the language, the user’s consent per purpose.
Related Adform Product and/or Service
Buy Side, Sell Side, DMP.
Legal bases
We process this data by default on the basis of our legitimate interest.
What channels does Adform operate in
1. Video channel
Description:
Video ads placed on phones, TVs, computers, gaming consoles, digital out of home signs and more.
Personal data categories:
1st Party IDs; Cookie IDs and other identifiers as applicable (e.g. MAIDs, IDFAs); IP address; Device type; Device location data (where available).
Legal basis of data processing:
Please refer to the section ‘What Information Do We Collect and Use’ for more information on exact lawful basis for each purpose.
Opt-out:
You may request to opt-out via the following link
here
.
2. Audio channel
Description:
Programmatic Audio runs on a range of services including Podcasts, Streaming Services and Digital Radio.
Personal data categories:
1st Party IDs; Cookies IDs and other identifiers as applicable (e.g. MAIDs, IDFAs); IP address; Device type; Device location data (where available).
Legal basis of data processing:
Please refer to the section ‘What Information Do We Collect and Use’ for more information on exact lawful basis for each purpose.
Opt-out:
You may request to opt-out via the following link
here
.
3. Gaming channel
Description:
In-game Advertising covers a range of gaming types from E-sport, Streaming and Platform games. The ad placements appear as game interruptions, outside of gaming area or in places which replicate advertising in real-world situations, such as advertising boards, product placements, mobile or static billboards.
Personal data categories:
1st Party IDs; Cookies IDs and other identifiers as applicable (e.g. MAIDs, IDFAs); IP address; Device type; Device location data (where available).
Legal basis of data processing:
Please refer to the section ‘What Information Do We Collect and Use’ for more information on exact lawful basis for each purpose.
Opt-out:
You may request to opt-out via the following link
here
.
4. DOOH channel
Description:
Digital Out Of Home (DOOH) refers to ads reaching the consumer while they are outside of their home, and targets people in transit, in public spaces, or during specific activities.
Personal data categories:
none.
Legal basis of data processing:
Legitimate interest.
Opt-out:
N/A.
5. CTV channel
Description:
Connected TV (CTV) refers to an internet-connected TV with built-in internet app capabilities.
Personal data categories:
1st Party IDs; Cookies IDs and other identifiers as applicable (e.g. MAIDs, IDFAs); IP address; Device type; Device location data (where available).
Legal basis of data processing:
Please refer to the section ‘What Information Do We Collect and Use’ for more information on exact lawful basis for each purpose.
Opt-out:
You may request to opt-out via the following link
here
.
6. Native ads channel
Description:
Native ads seamlessly match the content and design of the content it appears with. Native ads can be found in gaming, news, social media or other web or apps content outlets.
Personal data categories:
1st Party IDs; Cookies IDs and other identifiers as applicable (e.g. MAIDs, IDFAs); IP address; Device type; Device location data (where available).
Legal basis of data processing:
Please refer to the section ‘What Information Do We Collect and Use’ for more information on exact lawful basis for each purpose.
Opt-out:
You may request to opt-out via the following link
here
.
7. Display channel
Description:
Non-video, non-native banners that can be seen when browsing websites or using apps.
Personal data categories:
1st Party IDs; Cookies IDs and other identifiers as applicable (e.g. MAIDs, IDFAs); IP address; Device type; Device location data (where available).
Legal basis of data processing:
Please refer to the section ‘What Information Do We Collect and Use’ for more information on exact lawful basis for each purpose.
Opt-out:
You may request to opt-out via the following link
here
.
With whom we share Information
With clients
The Services allow clients to provide and share Information with each other. Clients have access to the Information they collect, upload or use within the Services, and may have access to Information generated through their use of the Service.
With third parties
We may share Cookie IDs or other IDs with partners for the purpose of ID synchronization. A list of such partners is available
here
.
We may also share Information with our affiliates and third-party services providers (list of Adform affiliates and third-party service providers (if applicable) is available
here
; who provide data processing services to us and support us in providing our Service (for example, to support the delivery of, provide functionality on, or help to enhance the security of our Service), or who otherwise process Information for purposes that are described in this Privacy Policy.
If instructed by our clients, we may also share Information that is controlled by our clients and which we process on behalf of our clients with third parties.
Also, we may disclose Information to the following categories of recipients:
To any competent law enforcement body, regulatory, government agency, court or other third party where we believe disclosure is necessary (i) as a matter of applicable law or regulation, (ii) to exercise, establish or defend our legal rights, or (iii) to protect your vital interests or those of any other person;
To any other person with your consent or with another suitable legal basis to the disclosure.
How long do we store Personal Information
We retain personal information we collect from you as long as we have an ongoing legitimate business need to do so (for example, to provide our clients with a service or to comply with applicable legal, tax or accounting requirements).
In the context of information derived from tracking technologies please note:
The cookies Adform sets in browsers expire 60 days after the last interaction with the website.
Mobile Advertising IDs are technical IDs in mobile application environments. Mobile Advertising IDs are resettable by the user; however, Adform does not have control of a Mobile Advertising ID. Adform will see the same Mobile Advertising ID as long as it is not changed by the device user or updated by the device.
Adform does not keep any Cookie-based Information longer than 13 months. In other words, any data that can be related to your internet devices are deleted after maximum 13 months.
International Data Transfers
Personal Information may be transferred to and processed in countries outside of the European Union. These countries may have data protection laws that are different from the laws of your country and, in some cases, may not be as protective.
Some of the recipients of Personal Information may operate outside the European Union (e.g. in the United States of America). This means that when we transfer your Personal Information to these third parties, your Personal Information will be processed outside the European Union. We have taken appropriate safeguards to ensure an adequate level of data protection in accordance with this Privacy Policy on the side of the recipients. For example, some of the transfers may occur to the so-called ‘adequate’ countries that ensure the same level of protection of Personal Information. Nevertheless, in case the data transfer occurs to a country that is not considered ‘adequate’, we have signed Standard Contractual Clauses as an international data transfer mechanism and conducted necessary supplementary measures, such as transfer risk assessments to ensure that the level of protection of your Personal Information is not lower than in the EU.
Your Data Protection Rights
You have the following data protection rights:
You can:
access,
correct,
update or
request deletion of,
object to processing of your personal information,
ask us to restrict processing of your personal information,
request portability of your personal information or
if we process your data with your consent, withdraw your consent at any time. The withdrawal of consent will not affect the lawfulness of processing based on consent before its withdrawal.
You can exercise these rights at any time by visiting the Data Subject Rights section via this
link
. You may also send an email to dpo[at]adform.com.
You have the right to complain to a data protection authority about our collection and use of your personal information. For more information, please contact your local data protection authority. A list of the European data protection authorities can be found here:
https://edpb.europa.eu/about-edpb/about-edpb/members_en
Contact Us
Controller for the processing of your personal data (alone or jointly with others) is:
Adform A/S
Silkegade 3B, ST. & 1., 1113 Copenhagen, Denmark
Adform has appointed a Data Protection Officer. If you have any questions or believe your personal information has been used in a way that is not consistent with this policy or applicable legislation, or you have any other data protection related issues or queries, please contact our Data Protection Officer by e-mail sent to dpo[at]adform.com.
Written inquiries may be addressed to:
Data Protection Officer
Adform A/S
Silkegade 3B, ST. & 1., 1113 Copenhagen, Denmark
Effective date of the recent update of this Privacy Policy 05.01.2024
